<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2011-07-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Presumptive bovine neonatal pancytopenia in a Holstein calf in Qu√©bec</TITLE><BODY>An 18-day-old heifer was presented with fever, depression, tachycardia, tachypnea, and prolonged bleeding time. Blood tests revealed severe anemia, thrombocytopenia, and leucopenia. The animal was negative by PCR for bovine virus diarrhea virus antigen. The findings supported a diagnosis of bovine neonatal pancytopenia. Treatments included fresh whole blood transfusion and antibiotics. The animal recovered fully.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>